<body>
    <h1>Kubernetes Cluster scanning with Kube bench tool on DIY Cluster</h1=
>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h2 id=3D"KubernetesClusterscanningwithKubebenchtoolonDIYCluster-Ho=
wtouseKubebenchtoperformKubernetesscanning:">How&nbsp;to&nbsp;use&nbsp;Kube=
bench&nbsp;to&nbsp;perform&nbsp;Kubernetes&nbsp;scanning:</h2>
<p>Here we suggest irrelevant ways to perform kube bench test on the DIY cl=
uster, which is a self managed kubernetes cluster.</p>
<h3 id=3D"KubernetesClusterscanningwithKubebenchtoolonDIYCluster-Installing=
fromacontainerandrunningtest">Installing from a container and running test<=
/h3>
<p>Run a container that installs kube-bench on the host, and then run kube-=
bench directly on the host.</p>
<ul>
<li><p>ssh to the master node:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">gcloud =
compute ssh dev-k8-master-01</pre>=20
</div>
</div></li>
<li><p>Execute the command:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">docker =
run --rm -v `pwd`:/host aquasec/kube-bench:latest install</pre>=20
</div>
</div><p>This command above copies the kube-bench binary and configuration =
files to your host from the Docker container.</p></li>
</ul>
<div id=3D"expander-1927021404" class=3D"expand-container">
<div id=3D"expander-control-1927021404" class=3D"expand-control">
<span class=3D"expand-control-icon"><img style=3D"vertical-align:middle;" c=
lass=3D"expand-control-image" src=3D"976345cb5c45a9cd04afeb0463f22a9d" widt=
h=3D"16" height=3D"16"></span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">kube-benc=
h file is stored on host</span>
</div>
<div id=3D"expander-content-1927021404" class=3D"expand-content">
<p>nacho@node1:~$ ls<br><strong>kube-bench</strong></p>
</div>
</div>
<ul>
<li><p>To perform the test simply run.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">./kube-=
bench</pre>=20
</div>
</div></li>
<li><p>The result displays on the terminal.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"KubernetesClusterscanningwithKubebenchtoolonDIYCluster-Runkube-be=
nchfrominsideacontainer">Run kube-bench from inside a container</h3>
<p>You can avoid installing kube-bench on the host by running it inside a c=
ontainer using the host PID namespace and mounting the&nbsp;/etc&nbsp;and&n=
bsp;/var&nbsp;directories where the configuration and other files are locat=
ed on the host so that kube-bench can check their existence and permissions=
.</p>
<ul>
<li><p>ssh to the master node:</p></li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">gcloud =
compute ssh dev-k8-master-01</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<ul>
<li><p>Execute the command:</p></li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">docker =
run --pid=3Dhost -v /etc:/etc:ro -v /var:/var:ro -t aquasec/kube-bench:late=
st --version 1.21</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<ul>
<li><p>The result displays on the terminal.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"KubernetesClusterscanningwithKubebenchtoolonDIYCluster-Runkubeben=
chasajob">Run kube bench as a job</h3>
<p>The <a href=3D"https://github.com/aquasecurity/kube-bench/blob/main/job.=
yaml" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">job.yaml</a> file can be app=
lied to run the tests as a job.</p>
<ul>
<li><p>Ssh to the bastion server.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">gcloud =
compute ssh dev-dr-bastion</pre>=20
</div>
</div></li>
<li><p>Clone the GitHub kube-bench repo.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">git clo=
ne https://github.com/aquasecurity/kube-bench.git
kubectl apply -f kube-bench/job.yaml</pre>=20
</div>
</div><p>job.batch/kube-bench created</p></li>
<li><p>Wait for a few seconds for the job to complete and corresponding pod=
 will completed status.</p></li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">kubectl=
 get job</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<div id=3D"expander-1212183837" class=3D"expand-container">
<div id=3D"expander-control-1212183837" class=3D"expand-control">
<span class=3D"expand-control-icon"><img style=3D"vertical-align:middle;" c=
lass=3D"expand-control-image" src=3D"976345cb5c45a9cd04afeb0463f22a9d" widt=
h=3D"16" height=3D"16"></span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Expand to=
 see an example</span>
</div>
<div id=3D"expander-content-1212183837" class=3D"expand-content">
<p>nacho@dev-dr-bastion:~/tools$ kubectl get job<br>NAME COMPLETIONS DURATI=
ON AGE<br>kube-bench 1/1 7s 41s<br>nacho@dev-dr-bastion:~/tools$ kubectl ge=
t pods<br>NAME READY STATUS RESTARTS AGE<br>kube-bench-rhxjh 0/1 Completed =
0 74s</p>
</div>
</div>
<ul>
<li><p>Review the result in the pod logs.</p></li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">kubectl=
 logs pod/'Name of kube-bench pod'</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<div id=3D"expander-1438227728" class=3D"expand-container">
<div id=3D"expander-control-1438227728" class=3D"expand-control">
<span class=3D"expand-control-icon"><img style=3D"vertical-align:middle;" c=
lass=3D"expand-control-image" src=3D"976345cb5c45a9cd04afeb0463f22a9d" widt=
h=3D"16" height=3D"16"></span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Expand to=
 review kube bench results in pod logs of our last example</span>
</div>
<div id=3D"expander-content-1438227728" class=3D"expand-content">
<p>nacho@dev-dr-bastion:~/tools$ kubectl logs pod/kube-bench-rhxjh<br>[INFO=
] 2 Etcd Node Configuration<br>[INFO] 2 Etcd Node Configuration Files</p>
</div>
</div>
    </div>
</body>
